 of Virginia|Independent Green]]\n|{{Party shading/Independent Green}} align=\"right\" |46,487\n|{{Party shading/Independent Green}} align=\"right\" |23%\n|-\n|[[United States House of Representatives elections in Virginia, 2008|2008]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|Andrea Miller}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |135,041\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |40%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''J. Randy Forbes'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |199,075\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |60%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House of Representatives elections in Virginia, 2010|2010]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|[[Wynne LeGrow]]}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |74,298\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |38%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''J. Randy Forbes'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |122,659\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |62%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House of Representatives elections in Virginia, 2012|2012]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|Ella Ward}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |150,190\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |43%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''J. Randy Forbes'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |199,292\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |57%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House of Representatives elections in Virginia, 2014|2014]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|Elliot Fausz}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |75,270\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |38%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''J. Randy Forbes'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |120,684\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |60%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |Bo Brown\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |[[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]]\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} align=\"right\" |4,427\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} align=\"right\" |2%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[United States House of Representatives elections in Virginia, 2016|2016]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''{{nowrap|Scott Taylor}}'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |21,406\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |53%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |J. Randy Forbes\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |16,552\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |41%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Pat Cardwell\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |2,773\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |7%\n|}\n\n{{refbegin}}\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Write-in and minor candidate notes:  In 2004, write-ins received 170 votes.  In 2006, write-ins received 886 votes. In 2008, write-ins received 405 votes. In 2010, write-ins received 432 votes. In 2014, write-ins received 257 votes.\n\n<nowiki>**</nowiki> Sisisky died on March 29, 2001; Forbes won the 2001 special election to fill out the remainder of his term.\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks}}\n* [http://forbes.house.gov/ Congressman J. Randy Forbes] official U.S. House site\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Virginia/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/J._Randy_Forbes_%5BR-4%5D|J. Randy Forbes}}\n* {{C-SPAN|jayforbes}}\n* [https://forbes.house.gov/chinacaucus/ Congressional China Caucus]\n* [http://www.sourcewatch.org/index.php?title=Randy_Forbes Profile] at [[SourceWatch]]\n* [http://hamptonroads.com/2011/11/us-house-approves-forbes-bill-god-we-trust-motto \"U.S. House approves Forbes' bill reaffirming 'In God We Trust'\"], ''Hampton Roads'', November 2, 2011\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Norman Sisisky]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from Virginia|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Virginia's 4th congressional district]]|years=2001\u2013present}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Donald McEachin]]<br>{{small|Elect}}}}\n|